from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

%matplotlib inline
In [2]:
def read_raw_image(url, rows, cols):
    fd = open(url, 'rb')
    file = np.fromfile( fd, dtype=np.uint8, count=rows*cols )
    fd.close()

    return file.reshape((rows, cols))

def show_images_with_plt( datas ):
    plt.figure(num=None, figsize=(18, 12), dpi=94 )
    for index, data in enumerate(datas):

        plt.subplot( len(datas)%3+1, 3, index+1 )
        plt.imshow( data["image"], cmap=plt.cm.gray, vmin=0, vmax=255 )
        plt.axis("off")
        plt.title(data["title"])

def show_images_hostogram( datas ):
    plt.figure(num=None, figsize=(18, 12), dpi=94 )
    for index, data in enumerate(datas):
        plt.subplot( len(datas)%3+1, 3, index+1 )
        plt.hist( data["image"].ravel(), bins=256, range=( 0, 255 ))
        plt.title(data["title"])

        "image": read_raw_image( "hw1/code/raw/sample1.raw", 256, 256 )

    },
    {
        "title":"power law",
        "image": read_raw_image( "hw1/code/problem0/B_power_law_1.2.raw", 256, 256 )
    }
]

show_images_with_plt( datas )
